ng people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from New York City]]\n[[Category:Singers from New York City]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actor}}\n{{BLP sources|date=July 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image       = <!-- only free-content images are allowed for depicting living people. Non-free and \"fair use\" images, e.g. promo photos, CD/DVD covers, posters, etc., will be deleted - see [[WP:NONFREE]] -->\n| name        = Jonathan Goldstein\n|birth_name = <!--don't add without a reliable source -->\n| birth_date= December 4, 1964 (age 53)\n| birth_place  = [[New York City, New York]], [[U.S]]\n| occupation  = Actor, director, musician\n| spouse = <!--don't add without a reliable source -->\n| years_active = 1989\u2013present\n}}\n'''Jonathan Goldstein''' is  an American actor, director and musician best known for his role as Walter Nichols in the [[Nickelodeon]] [[sitcom]] ''[[Drake & Josh]]'' (2004\u20132007).\n\n==Life and career==\nSome of his other television credits include ''[[The Riches]]'', ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]'', ''[[NCIS (TV series)|NCIS]]'', ''[[Heroes (U.S. TV series)|Heroes]]'', ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'', ''[[Once and Again]]'' and  ''[[The Electric Company (2009 TV series)|The Electric Company]]''. He also directed three episodes of the Nickelodeon sitcom ''[[iCarly]]'' starring his former ''Drake & Josh'' co-star [[Miranda Cosgrove]].\n\nGoldstein was also a founding member of Los Angeles's [[Sacred Fools Theater Company]] and served as one of its Artistic Directors during the theater's inaugural season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sacredfools.org/members.htm|title=SACRED FOOLS Members & Staff}} Sacred Fools Theater Company</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sacredfools.org/archives.htm#1|title=SACRED FOOLS Past Productions}} Sacred Fools Theater Company</ref>\n\nIn later years, Goldstein has taken to traveling to [[Bowling Green, Kentucky]] during the summer to direct amateur youth theater. So far, he has directed local productions of ''[[Romeo and Juliet]]'',  ''[[Pride and Prejudice]]'', and ''[[The Crucible]]''.\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film.===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Film\n!Role\n!class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''The Jitters''\n| Joey\n| Debut \n|-\n| 1993\n| ''Stranger''\n| \n| \n|-\n| 1996\n| ''Body of Influence 2''\n| Rick Benson\n| \n|-\n| 1998\n| ''Shock Television''\n| Donut Shop Owner\n| \n|-\n| 1999\n| ''The Auteur Theory''\n| Santa Claus\n|\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''Tube''\n| Eric\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''The Guru Singh-Cinderelli''\n| Max\n| Short video\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''Herstory''\n| Mark\n| \n|-\n| 2009\n| ''Table Manners''\n| Mrs. Hayward\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''No Heart Feelings''\n| Joe (voice)\n| \n|-\n| 2012\n| ''Unorthodox''\n| Morty\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Teacher of the Year (film)|Teacher of the Year]]''\n| John Collier\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''Flashout''\n| Repairman \n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Film\n!Role\n!class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''Target of Suspicion''\n| Bartender\n| Television movie\n|- \n| 1997\n| ''Ma\u00eetre Da Costa''\n|Le doigt de Dieu\n| \n|- \n| 1999\n| ''[[Wasteland (American TV series)|Wasteland]]''\n| Cigarette Guy\n| \n|-\n| 2000\u20132001\n| ''[[Once and Again]]''\n| Fosdick\n| \n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]''\n| Mike\n| Episode: \"[[Life Serial]]\"\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Without a Trace]]''\n| Bartender\n| \n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[The Handler (TV series)|The Handler]]''\n| Paramedic\n| \n|-\n| 2004\u20132007\n| ''[[Drake & Josh]]''\n| Walter Nichols\n| 56 episodes\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Half & Half]]''\n| Photographer\n|\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[The West Wing]]''\n| Knocking Congressman\n| \n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Drake & Josh Go Hollywood]]''\n| Walter Nichols\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[The Wedding Bells]]''\n| Bar Guy\n| \n|-\n| 2007\u20132008\n| ''[[The Riches]]''\n| Wes\n| \n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[The Starter Wife (TV series)|The Starter Wife]]''\n| Bill\n| \n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Californication (TV series)|Californication]]''\n| Mario\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Merry Christmas, Drake & Josh]]''\n| Walter Nichols\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Eleventh Hour (U.S. TV series)|Eleventh Hour]]''\n| Charlie Wease\n| \n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Meteor (TV miniseries)|Meteor]]''\n| Walt Payne\n| Mini-series\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Party Down]]''\n| Douglas\n|\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Heroes (U.S. TV series)|Heroes]]''\n| Male Citizen\n| \n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Private Practice (TV series)|Private Practice]]''\n| Rabbi\n| \n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Parks and Recreation]]''\n| Donnie Rotger\n| Episode: \"Christmas Scandal\"\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]''\n| Ken May\n| \n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Criminal Minds]]''\n| Detective John Fordham\n| \n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[The Defenders (2010 TV series)|The Defenders]]''\n| Luke Purcell\n| \n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[NCIS (TV series)|NCIS]]''\n| Glenn Block\n|\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Svetlana (TV series)|Svetlana]]''\n| \n|Episode # 2.12 \n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Workaholics]]''\n| Father\n| \n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Fear the Walking Dead]]''\n| Alan \n| Episode: \"[[Ouroboros]]\"\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Lucifer (TV series)|Lucifer]]''\n| Jonathan Burke\n| Episode: \"Boo Normal\"\n|-\n|2019\n| ''[[Magnum P.I. (2018 TV series)|Magnum P.I.]]''\n| Roland McDowell\n| Episode: \"Black is the Widow\"\n|-\n|2019\n|Adaptation \n|Larry \n|Filming \n|}\n\n=== Video games ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[CSI: NY (video game)|CSI: NY]]''\n| Steven Benson\n| \n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[BioShock 2]]''\n| Additional Voices\n| [[BioShock 2: Minerva's Den|Minerva's Den]] DLC\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|0326245|Jonathan Goldstein}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Goldstein, Jonathan}}\n[[Category:20th-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from New York City]]\n[[Category:Singers from New York City]]\n", "name_user": "EdmundT", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jonathan_Goldstein_(actor)"}
{"title_page": "Dr. Heinz Doofenshmirtz", "text_new": "{{Infobox character\n| colour      = brown\n| name        = Dr.Heinz Doofenshmirtz\n| series      = [[Phineas and Ferb]] / [[Milo Murphy's Law]]\n| image       = Heinz Doofenshmirtz.png \n| image_size  = 170px\n| first       = {{Plainlist|\n* \"[[Rollercoaster (Phineas and Ferb)|Rollercoaster]]\" (2007; Phineas and Ferb)\n}}\n| last             = \n| creator     = [[Dan Povenmire]]<br />[[Jeff \"Swampy\" Marsh]]\n| voice       = Dan Povenmire\n| alias       = Doof<br>Dr. D<br>Stouchy<br>Heinz the Ocelot<br>Professor Time\n| occupation  = Evil Scientist (formerly)<br>High School Science Teacher (formerly)<br>Mayor of Danville<br>O.W.C.A agent<br>Professor of Time<br>Garden Gnome (formerly)\n| lbl21       = Affiliation \n| data21      = L.O.V.E.M.U.F.F.I.N. (formerly)<br><small>(League of Villainous Evildoers Maniacally United For Frightening Investments in Naughtiness)</small><br>O.W.C.A.<br><small>(Organisation Without a Cool Acronym)</small>\n| spouse      = [[Charlene Doofenshmirtz]] (divorced)\n| children    = [[Vanessa Doofenshmirtz]] (daughter)\n| family      = [[List of Phineas and Ferb characters#Roger Doofenshmirtz|Roger Doofenshmirtz]] (brother)\n| relatives   = \n| noinfo      = yes\n| nationality = Drusselsteinian\n}}\n'''Dr. Heinz \"Doof\" Doofenshmirtz''' (also known as '''Dr. D''' and later '''Professor Time''') is a main character from the American animated television series ''[[Phineas and Ferb]]'' and ''[[Milo Murphy's Law]]''. He was created by [[Dan Povenmire]] and [[Jeff \"Swampy\" Marsh]], and is voiced by Povenmire. The character first appeared in the pilot episode of ''Phineas and Ferb''. He is described as an incompetent and forgetful [[evil scientist]] intent on conquering the \"entire tri-state area\" by creating obscure but nefarious inventions, despite not technically being a true villain and has a good side on some occasions. By the time of ''[[O.W.C.A. Files]]'' and ''Milo Murphy's Law'', the character is redeemed, using his inventions for the good of the world and looking after his daughter Vanessa. Dr. Doofenshmirtz speaks with a caricature of a [[German language|German]] accent and is from the fictional [[Europe]]an country Drusselstein.\n\nDoofenshmirtz appears in several merchandise pieces, including the book series<ref name=\"Book1\">{{cite book|last=Jones|first=Jasmine|title=Speed Demons|url=https://archive.org/details/speeddemons0000jone|url-access=registration|publisher=Disney Press|isbn=1-4231-1628-3|year=2009}}</ref><ref name=\"Book2\">{{cite book|last=Bergen|first=Lara Rice|title=Runaway Hit|publisher=Disney Press|isbn=1-4231-1797-2|year=2009|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/runawayhit0000berg}}</ref><ref name=\"Book3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.google.com/products/catalog?q=Phineas+and+Ferb+books&oe=utf-8&cid=14715976473066931833&sa=title#ps-sellers|title=Wild Surprise.|work=Google Shopping}}</ref><ref name=\"Book4\">{{cite web|url=http://www.google.com/products/catalog?q=Phineas+and+Ferb+books&oe=utf-8&cid=14829553982344007318&sa=title#ps-sellers|title=Thrill-o-rama.|work=Google Shopping}}</ref> and the video game.<ref name=\"Game\">{{cite web|url=http://www.kidzworld.com/article/16586-phineas-and-ferb-ds-game-review |title=Phineas and Ferb :: DS Game Review |publisher=Kidzworld |date= |accessdate=2009-05-02}}</ref> He later made an appearance in the ''[[Milo Murphy's Law]]'' episode \"Fungus Among Us\";<ref>https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/phineas-and-ferb-dr-doofenshmirtz-milo-murphys-law-crossover-disney-xd-1202574269/</ref> following his house being destroyed in the second season premiere, he begins to live in the Murphys' house, and subsequently becomes a main character in the series.<ref>http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/milo-murphys-law-phineas-ferb-crossover-is-coming-1022459</ref>\n\n==Role in ''Phineas and Ferb''==\nDoofenshmirtz is portrayed as a bumbling, dimwitted evil genius. He strives to take over the \"entire [[tri-state area]]\"<ref name=\"FS\" group=\"epnote\">{{cite episode|title=Flop Starz|series=Phineas and Ferb|season=1|number=4 (P.2)|credits=Writers: Sherm Cohen, Antoine Guilbaud; Director: Dan Povenmire|network=Disney Channel}}</ref> by using peculiar contraptions made up of \"strange items [he] purchases off the internet\".<ref name=\"IAT\" group=\"epnote\">{{cite episode|title=It's About Time!|series=Phineas and Ferb| season= 1|number= 9|credits=Writer and Director: Dan Povenmire|network=Disney Channel}}</ref> His nemesis is [[Perry the Platypus]], a skilled [[anthropomorphic]] [[platypus]] [[espionage|secret agent]] who disguises himself as the mindless pet of the series' title characters.\n\nA typical episode features Doofenshmirtz hatching an evil scheme or invention that he often links to a \"[[Flashback (narrative)|back story]]\" from his youth. The stories explore his mentally abusive childhood at the hands of his cold and apparently shallow parents in the fictional village of Gimmelshtump, Drusselstein, where his brother, [[List of Phineas and Ferb characters#Roger Doofenshmirtz|Roger]], is favored over him.<ref name=\"podcast\">{{cite news|url= http://downloads.wired.com/podcasts/assets/thegeekdads/thegeekdadsspecialphineasandferb.mp3?_kip_ipx=1895089171-1238013329|title= \"The Geek Dads\" Podcast interview with Povenmire & Marsh | work=Wired}}</ref> Doofenshmirtz usually has long [[monologues]]<ref name=\"podcast\"/> and displays acts of \"cartoonish\" physical violence<ref name=\"IAT\" group=\"epnote\"/> towards [[Perry the Platypus]]. Often his inventions achieve a single successful shot before being destroyed. This shot usually serves to destroy [[Phineas Flynn|Phineas]] and [[Ferb Fletcher|Ferb's]] inventions, preventing their sister, [[Candace Flynn|Candace]] from 'busting' them, i.e. showing their creations to their mother. According to his own life story, he was a [[bratwurst]] salesman, before being ruined by the [[hot dog]] industry; only then did he become an evil scientist.\n\nIn ''[[Phineas and Ferb the Movie: Across the 2nd Dimension]]'', a more intelligent and successful version of Dr. Doofenshmirtz (from an alternate reality) appears, with the regular Dr. Doofenshmirtz serving as a supporting character. The alternate Doofenshmirtz later returns in the episode sequel, ''Tales from the Resistance: Back to the 2nd Dimension''.\n\nDespite nearly failing in almost all of his schemes, there are a few times when Doofenshmirtz actually succeeds. One example is in the episode \"Candace Disconnected\", where he builds a Pick 'Em Up-Inator to successfully pick up his daughter from her school and bring her home in a couple of seconds. Another time is in the [[Phineas and Ferb the Movie: Across the 2nd Dimension|TV film]], when he built an Otherdimension-Inator that involves traveling to alternate dimensions; this is done with the help from Phineas and Ferb, much to Perry's distress. In the episode \"Cranius Maximus\", Doofenshmirtz builds a Key-Find-Inator to successfully steal the Key to the City, something which Perry failed to stop. Another example, which is perhaps the most famous, is in the 2014 special \"Phineas and Ferb Save Summer\", when Doofenshmirtz builds an -inator that uses the mass of the planet Jupiter to move the Earth away from the Sun into an early autumn. Despite being beaten by Perry with a mop, Doofenshmirtz manages to succeed in moving the Earth anyway, much to Perry's dismay. It also may have allowed him to briefly take over the Tri-State Area, as the change in weather caused civil unrest and allowed Doofenshmirtz and his fellow villains to take over City Hall.\n\nIn the [[series finale]] \"Last Day of Summer\", Doofenshmritz built an -inator that involves building a Tri-Governor's Mansion to Danville so that he can be elected as the first Tri-Governor of the Tri-State Area. Through a series of time loops (caused by his Do-Over-Inator, which was activated by [[Candace Flynn|Candace]]), Doof anticipates Perry's every move and defeats him in a series of traps before proceeding with his scheme, which became a complete success. He even took the opportunity to write up a law forbidding Perry and his agents from thwarting him until his term is over, which left Perry very depressed and admitting defeat. Despite succeeding in his lifelong goal, Doof learns that Vanessa wants to have an internship at O.W.C.A. and that his job as Tri-Governor is preventing her from joining the internship, leaving her depressed as well. Deciding that her happiness is more important than his evil ways, Doof decides to give them up, change for the better and allow Vanessa to have the internship. Following this, Doof also becomes a member of O.W.C.A.\n\n=== Running gags ===\nDr. Doofenshmirtz is a part of various [[running gag]]s in ''Phineas and Ferb''. One is his redundant naming of inventions, which almost always end with the [[suffix]] \"inator\".<ref name=\"MB\" group=\"epnote\">{{cite episode|title=Mom's Birthday|season=1|network=Disney Channel|series=Phineas and Ferb|number=11|credits=Director: Zac Moncrief}}</ref> Furthermore, Dr. Doofenshmirtz only recognizes the hat-wearing version of Perry. During every introduction of Dr. Doofenshmirtz in the episodes, the audience (and sometimes the characters), hears the ring tone of Doofenshmirtz, typically with the words \"Doofenshmirtz Evil Incorporated\", and is almost always sung by a quartet.<ref name=\"jcc\" group=\"epnote\">{{cite episode|title=Attack of the 50 Foot Sister|series=[[Phineas and Ferb]]| season= 2|episode= 51|credits=Writer: Jon Colton Barry, Piero Piluso; Director: [[Zac Moncrief]]|network=[[Disney XD]]}}</ref> Habitually, Doofenshmirtz's daily encounters with Perry follow a chain of events that routinely begins with a [[back-story]] told by Doofenshmirtz<ref name=\"Meap\" group=\"epnote\">{{cite episode|title=The Chronicles of Meap|series=Phineas and Ferb|number=59|season=2|network=Disney XD}}</ref><ref name=\"Plane\" group=\"epnote\">{{cite episode|title=De Plane! De Plane!|season=2|series=Phineas and Ferb|network=Disney XD}}</ref> and ends with Doofenshmirtz yelling his [[catch phrase]], \"Curse you, Perry the Platypus!\" Conveniently, he installs [[self-destruct]] buttons on everything he owns, which is usually how Perry destroys his creations. The residents of the town of Danville often mistake Doofenshmirtz for a pharmacist because he is always wearing a white lab coat. This theme was featured in a two-part 2014 Halloween episode entitled \"Night of the Living Pharmacists\".\n\n==Role in ''Milo Murphy's Law''==\n\nDoof makes a [[cameo appearance]] in the ending cliffhanger of the season finale of ''[[Milo Murphy's Law]]'', and tries to become a good guy throughout the [[Milo Murphy's Law#Season 2 (2019)|second season]].\n\n== Creation and design ==\n[[File:Dan Povenmire Comic-Con 2009.jpg|thumb|245px|Doofenshmirtz is voiced by ''Phineas and Ferb'' co-creator [[Dan Povenmire]].<ref name=\"podcast\"/>]]\nWhen [[Jeff \"Swampy\" Marsh]] and [[Dan Povenmire]] worked on the [[Nickelodeon (TV channel)|Nickelodeon]] animated series ''[[Rocko's Modern Life]],'' they always included a song/musical number and an action/chase scene. They wanted to incorporate this trait in \"Phineas and Ferb\",<ref name=\"AM2\">{{cite web|url= http://mag.awn.com/index.php?ltype=pageone&category2=&article_no=3534&page=2|title= From Swampy & Dan Emerges Phineas and Ferb\", Page 2.|author= Strike, Joe.|work= Animation World Magazine|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090821165941/http://mag.awn.com/index.php?ltype=pageone&category2=&article_no=3534&page=2|archivedate= 2009-08-21}}</ref> and used a platypus secret agent,<ref name=\"tampa\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tampabay.com/features/parenting/article993119.ece|title=Quick wit, funny characters drive ''Phineas and Ferb''|author=Robinson, Sherry|date=2009-04-18|accessdate=2009-08-16|work=[[St. Petersburg Times]]|location=[[St. Petersburg, Florida]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110607055650/http://www.tampabay.com/features/parenting/article993119.ece|archive-date=2011-06-07|url-status=dead}}</ref> due to its interesting appearance <ref name=\"QA\">{{cite news|url= http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/news/e3i0bc78baf8235f8b4159fd786ff9f8736|title= Q&A: Dan Povenmire|author= Bond, Paul.|date= 7 June 2009|work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> and role as a continuous nemesis that viewers could become familiar with.<ref>{{cite video|url=http://www.audiohollywood.net/Audio/phineas_ferb.mp3|title=\"Phineas and Ferb\" creators Dan Povenmire and Swampy Marsh|publisher=Audioholywood.net|medium=Audio interview|accessdate=2009-08-01|date=2009-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120301105638/http://www.audiohollywood.net/Audio/phineas_ferb.mp3|archive-date=2012-03-01|url-status=dead}}</ref> \"Dr. Meddleshmirtz,\" which later changed to Doofenshmirtz,<ref name=\"OPD\">{{cite video|title=Original Pitch featurette for Volume I|medium=DVD|people=Povenmire, Dan|publisher=[[Disney DVD]]}}</ref> was created in the same vein.\n\nEvery main character of the series was designed using the geometric shapes of  [[Tex Avery]]'s ''[[Looney Tunes]]'' graphic style in mind - Doofenshmirtz appears to be an [[oval]].<ref name=\"AM2\"/> The simplicity of the drawings were intended to allow child viewers to copy them easily. Each one was designed to be recognizable from a distance or, as Povenmire notes as a reference to [[Matt Groening]] and ''[[The Simpsons]],'' by [[silhouette]].<ref name=\"411 news\">{{cite web|url=http://www.resource411.com/411Update/Issue/Articles/Story.cfm?StoryID=1020 |title=Phineas and Ferb: Music, Mischief, And The Endless Summer Vacation |work=411 News |author=Galas, Marjorie |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090607043445/http://www.resource411.com/411Update/Issue/Articles/Story.cfm?StoryID=1020 |archivedate=2009-06-07 }}</ref>\n\n===Voice===\nCo-creator and executive producer Dan Povenmire voices Doofenshmirtz. He describes the voice he uses as \"Eastern European\" and is one he used at the age of fifteen while having pillow fights with his five-year-old sister. To this day, his sister recognizes the voice and asks him to do it frequently. During recording sessions, Povenmire is easily able to ad-lib and [[improvise]]; the writers can change his lines without throwing him off.<ref name=\"podcast\"/> Povenmire sometimes even adds his own lines or alters his enunciation{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}, and is usually asked to perform the voice in interviews.<ref name=\"podcast\"/>\n\n==Reception==\nDespite a negative review of the ''Phineas and Ferb'' series on ''Toon Zone'', Maxie Zeus notes that Povenmire's performance as Doofenshmirtz is a strong point of the series. Zeus states that \"Dan Povenmire voices him with such energy, and with such perfect timing, that you'll laugh out loud even at the stuff that isn't even ''supposed'' to be funny.\" Zeus also says that the Doofenshmirtz subplot would have made a \"fine bit of sketch writing\" if trimmed down.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.toonzone.net/articles/21300/phineas-and-ferb-spawn-of-frankenstein|title=\"Phineas and Ferb\": Spawn of Frankenstein|work=Toon Zone|last=Zeus|first=Maxie|date=February 1, 2008|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090822024814/http://news.toonzone.net/articles/21300/phineas-and-ferb-spawn-of-frankenstein|archivedate=August 22, 2009}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, Josh Jackson, editor-in-chief for ''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste Magazine]],'' wrote in a blog that ''Phineas and Ferb'' was \"the best kids show on TV\" and gave Doofenshmirtz a large amount of praise. Jackson calls his inventions \"awesomely designated devices of pure evil\" and his complex relationship with his nemesis Perry the Platypus as \"pitch-perfect.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pastemagazine.com/blogs/lists/2009/03/7-reasons-why-phineas-and-ferb-is-the-best-kids-sh.html|title=Five Reasons Why ''Phineas and Ferb'' is the Best Kids Show on TV|work=Paste Magazine|last=Jackson | first = John  |date=March 31, 2009}}</ref>\n\n==''Doof's Daily Dirt'' webseries ==\nIn January 2013, Doofenshmirtz \"launched [his] own YouTube channel and weekly videocast\" titled ''Doof's Daily Dirt''.{{efn|In one of the ''Doof's Daily Dirt'' videocasts, Doofenshmirtz admits that he chose Daily because of the title's [[alliteration]].}}  He comments on various [[Internet meme]]s and pop culture trends, usually long after the subject is no longer of interest or relevance. Subjects have included [[Facebook]], [[Internet slang|Internet Acronyms]], [[Lolcatz]], Bacon-infused products, [[Psy]]'s \"[[Gangnam Style]]\", [[One Direction]], [[Carly Rae Jepsen]]'s \"[[Call Me Maybe]]\", [[Here Comes Honey Boo Boo|Honey Boo-Boo]], the [[Keeping Up with the Kardashians|Kardashians]] and the [[Mayan apocalypse]]. He also started a Twitter account where he posts frequently.<ref name=\"wired\">{{cite web\n| url = https://www.wired.com/geekdad/2013/01/doofenshmirtz-daily-dirt/\n| title = Exclusive: Phineas and Ferb\u2018s Dr. Doofenshmirtz Launches Web Series, Twitter Account\n| last = Blum | first = Matt\n| work = Geekdad - Wired.com\n| date = January 4, 2013\n}}</ref> The webisode series had an original run of 13 episodes.<ref>{{cite web\n| url = http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/01/04/phineas-ferb-character-dr-doofenshmirtz-makes-his-social-media-debut-with-new-twitter-account-and-web-series/163984/\n| title = 'Phineas & Ferb' Character Dr. Doofenshmirtz Makes His Social Media Debut With New Twitter Account and Web Series\n| work = TV By the Numbers\n| last = Bibel | first = Sara\n| date = January 4, 2013\n}}</ref> He appeared in the season finale for the reality TV series ''[[Shark Tank]]'' to pitch his latest invention.<ref>{{cite web\n| url = http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2013/04/22/phineas-and-ferbs-nefarious-dr-doofenshmirtz-pitches-shark-tank-to-get-a-deal-for-his-latest-evil-inator-invention-820111/20130422disney01/\n| title = April 22, 2013\n| work = The Futon Critic\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2013/tv/news/phineas-and-ferb-villain-takes-pitch-to-shark-tank-in-disney-channel-abc-crossover-1200482912/|title=\u2018Phineas and Ferb\u2019 Villain Takes Pitch to \u2018Shark Tank\u2019 in Disney Channel-ABC Crossover|first=Marc |last=Graser|date=May 17, 2013|work=Variety|accessdate=9 July 2015}}</ref> The web series was renewed for a second season, but ultimately was ended after the cancellation of Phineas and Ferb.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2013/07/12/phineas-and-ferbs-breakout-internet-star-dr-doofenshmirtz-is-back-online-with-26-new-webisodes-for-summer-107515/20130712disney02/|title=Breaking News - \"Phineas and Ferb's\" Breakout Internet Star Dr. Doofenshmirtz Is Back Online with 26 New Webisodes for Summer|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|author=|date=|accessdate=9 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n'''Episode references'''\n{{reflist|group=\"epnote\"|40em}}\n\n'''Other sources'''\n{{Reflist|40em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{YouTube|u=doofdaily|Doof's Daily Dirt}}\n\n{{Phineas and Ferb}}\n{{Works by Dan Povenmire and Jeff \"Swampy\" Marsh}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Doofenshmirtz, Dr. Heinz}}\n[[Category:Phineas and Ferb characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional mad scientists]]\n[[Category:Fictional hunchbacks]]\n[[Category:Fictional inventors]]\n[[Category:Television characters introduced in 2007]]\n[[Category:Fictional American people of German descent]]\n[[Category:Animated human characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional immigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Male characters in animation]]\n[[Category:Milo Murphy's Law]]\n\n[[he:\u05d3\"\u05e8 \u05d4\u05d9\u05d9\u05e0\u05e5 \u05d3\u05d5\u05e4\u05e0\u05e9\u05de\u05d9\u05e8\u05e5]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox character\n| colour      = brown\n| name        = Dr.Heinz Doofenshmirtz\n| series      = [[Phineas and Ferb]] / [[Milo Murphy's Law]]\n| image       = Heinz Doofenshmirtz.png \n| image_size  = 170px\n| first       = {{Plainlist|\n* \"[[Rollercoaster (Phineas and Ferb)|Rollercoaster]]\" (2007; Phineas and Ferb)\n}}\n| last             = \n| creator     = [[Dan Povenmire]]<br />[[Jeff \"Swampy\" Marsh]]\n| voice       = Dan Povenmire\n| alias       = Doof<br>Dr. D<br>Stouchy<br>Heinz the Ocelot<br>Professor Time\n| occupation  = Evil Scientist (formerly)<br>High School Science Teacher (formerly)<br>Mayor of Danville<br>O.W.C.A agent<br>Professor of Time\n| lbl21       = Affiliation \n| data21      = L.O.V.E.M.U.F.F.I.N. (formerly)<br><small>(League of Villainous Evildoers Maniacally United For Frightening Investments in Naughtiness)</small><br>O.W.C.A.<br><small>(Organisation Without a Cool Acronym)</small>\n| spouse      = [[Charlene Doofenshmirtz]] (divorced)\n| children    = [[Vanessa Doofenshmirtz]] (daughter)\n| family      = [[List of Phineas and Ferb characters#Roger Doofenshmirtz|Roger Doofenshmirtz]] (brother)\n| relatives   = \n| noinfo      = yes\n| nationality = Drusselsteinian\n}}\n'''Dr. Heinz \"Doof\" Doofenshmirtz''' (also known as '''Dr. D''' and later '''Professor Time''') is a main character from the American animated television series ''[[Phineas and Ferb]]'' and ''[[Milo Murphy's Law]]''. He was created by [[Dan Povenmire]] and [[Jeff \"Swampy\" Marsh]], and is voiced by Povenmire. The character first appeared in the pilot episode of ''Phineas and Ferb''. He is described as an incompetent and forgetful [[evil scientist]] intent on conquering the \"entire tri-state area\" by creating obscure but nefarious inventions, despite not technically being a true villain and has a good side on some occasions. By the time of ''[[O.W.C.A. Files]]'' and ''Milo Murphy's Law'', the character is redeemed, using his inventions for the good of the world and looking after his daughter Vanessa. Dr. Doofenshmirtz speaks with a caricature of a [[German language|German]] accent and is from the fictional [[Europe]]an country Drusselstein.\n\nDoofenshmirtz appears in several merchandise pieces, including the book series<ref name=\"Book1\">{{cite book|last=Jones|first=Jasmine|title=Speed Demons|url=https://archive.org/details/speeddemons0000jone|url-access=registration|publisher=Disney Press|isbn=1-4231-1628-3|year=2009}}</ref><ref name=\"Book2\">{{cite book|last=Bergen|first=Lara Rice|title=Runaway Hit|publisher=Disney Press|isbn=1-4231-1797-2|year=2009|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/runawayhit0000berg}}</ref><ref name=\"Book3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.google.com/products/catalog?q=Phineas+and+Ferb+books&oe=utf-8&cid=14715976473066931833&sa=title#ps-sellers|title=Wild Surprise.|work=Google Shopping}}</ref><ref name=\"Book4\">{{cite web|url=http://www.google.com/products/catalog?q=Phineas+and+Ferb+books&oe=utf-8&cid=14829553982344007318&sa=title#ps-sellers|title=Thrill-o-rama.|work=Google Shopping}}</ref> and the video game.<ref name=\"Game\">{{cite web|url=http://www.kidzworld.com/article/16586-phineas-and-ferb-ds-game-review |title=Phineas and Ferb :: DS Game Review |publisher=Kidzworld |date= |accessdate=2009-05-02}}</ref> He later made an appearance in the ''[[Milo Murphy's Law]]'' episode \"Fungus Among Us\";<ref>https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/phineas-and-ferb-dr-doofenshmirtz-milo-murphys-law-crossover-disney-xd-1202574269/</ref> following his house being destroyed in the second season premiere, he begins to live in the Murphys' house, and subsequently becomes a main character in the series.<ref>http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/milo-murphys-law-phineas-ferb-crossover-is-coming-1022459</ref>\n\n==Role in ''Phineas and Ferb''==\nDoofenshmirtz is portrayed as a bumbling, dimwitted evil genius. He strives to take over the \"entire [[tri-state area]]\"<ref name=\"FS\" group=\"epnote\">{{cite episode|title=Flop Starz|series=Phineas and Ferb|season=1|number=4 (P.2)|credits=Writers: Sherm Cohen, Antoine Guilbaud; Director: Dan Povenmire|network=Disney Channel}}</ref> by using peculiar contraptions made up of \"strange items [he] purchases off the internet\".<ref name=\"IAT\" group=\"epnote\">{{cite episode|title=It's About Time!|series=Phineas and Ferb| season= 1|number= 9|credits=Writer and Director: Dan Povenmire|network=Disney Channel}}</ref> His nemesis is [[Perry the Platypus]], a skilled [[anthropomorphic]] [[platypus]] [[espionage|secret agent]] who disguises himself as the mindless pet of the series' title characters.\n\nA typical episode features Doofenshmirtz hatching an evil scheme or invention that he often links to a \"[[Flashback (narrative)|back story]]\" from his youth. The stories explore his mentally abusive childhood at the hands of his cold and apparently shallow parents in the fictional village of Gimmelshtump, Drusselstein, where his brother, [[List of Phineas and Ferb characters#Roger Doofenshmirtz|Roger]], is favored over him.<ref name=\"podcast\">{{cite news|url= http://downloads.wired.com/podcasts/assets/thegeekdads/thegeekdadsspecialphineasandferb.mp3?_kip_ipx=1895089171-1238013329|title= \"The Geek Dads\" Podcast interview with Povenmire & Marsh | work=Wired}}</ref> Doofenshmirtz usually has long [[monologues]]<ref name=\"podcast\"/> and displays acts of \"cartoonish\" physical violence<ref name=\"IAT\" group=\"epnote\"/> towards [[Perry the Platypus]]. Often his inventions achieve a single successful shot before being destroyed. This shot usually serves to destroy [[Phineas Flynn|Phineas]] and [[Ferb Fletcher|Ferb's]] inventions, preventing their sister, [[Candace Flynn|Candace]] from 'busting' them, i.e. showing their creations to their mother. According to his own life story, he was a [[bratwurst]] salesman, before being ruined by the [[hot dog]] industry; only then did he become an evil scientist.\n\nIn ''[[Phineas and Ferb the Movie: Across the 2nd Dimension]]'', a more intelligent and successful version of Dr. Doofenshmirtz (from an alternate reality) appears, with the regular Dr. Doofenshmirtz serving as a supporting character. The alternate Doofenshmirtz later returns in the episode sequel, ''Tales from the Resistance: Back to the 2nd Dimension''.\n\nDespite nearly failing in almost all of his schemes, there are a few times when Doofenshmirtz actually succeeds. One example is in the episode \"Candace Disconnected\", where he builds a Pick 'Em Up-Inator to successfully pick up his daughter from her school and bring her home in a couple of seconds. Another time is in the [[Phineas and Ferb the Movie: Across the 2nd Dimension|TV film]], when he built an Otherdimension-Inator that involves traveling to alternate dimensions; this is done with the help from Phineas and Ferb, much to Perry's distress. In the episode \"Cranius Maximus\", Doofenshmirtz builds a Key-Find-Inator to successfully steal the Key to the City, something which Perry failed to stop. Another example, which is perhaps the most famous, is in the 2014 special \"Phineas and Ferb Save Summer\", when Doofenshmirtz builds an -inator that uses the mass of the planet Jupiter to move the Earth away from the Sun into an early autumn. Despite being beaten by Perry with a mop, Doofenshmirtz manages to succeed in moving the Earth anyway, much to Perry's dismay. It also may have allowed him to briefly take over the Tri-State Area, as the change in weather caused civil unrest and allowed Doofenshmirtz and his fellow villains to take over City Hall.\n\nIn the [[series finale]] \"Last Day of Summer\", Doofenshmritz built an -inator that involves building a Tri-Governor's Mansion to Danville so that he can be elected as the first Tri-Governor of the Tri-State Area. Through a series of time loops (caused by his Do-Over-Inator, which was activated by [[Candace Flynn|Candace]]), Doof anticipates Perry's every move and defeats him in a series of traps before proceeding with his scheme, which became a complete success. He even took the opportunity to write up a law forbidding Perry and his agents from thwarting him until his term is over, which left Perry very depressed and admitting defeat. Despite succeeding in his lifelong goal, Doof learns that Vanessa wants to have an internship at O.W.C.A. and that his job as Tri-Governor is preventing her from joining the internship, leaving her depressed as well. Deciding that her happiness is more important than his evil ways, Doof decides to give them up, change for the better and allow Vanessa to have the internship. Following this, Doof also becomes a member of O.W.C.A.\n\n=== Running gags ===\nDr. Doofenshmirtz is a part of various [[running gag]]s in ''Phineas and Ferb''. One is his redundant naming of inventions, which almost always end with the [[suffix]] \"inator\".<ref name=\"MB\" group=\"epnote\">{{cite episode|title=Mom's Birthday|season=1|network=Disney Channel|series=Phineas and Ferb|number=11|credits=Director: Zac Moncrief}}</ref> Furthermore, Dr. Doofenshmirtz only recognizes the hat-wearing version of Perry. During every introduction of Dr. Doofenshmirtz in the episodes, the audience (and sometimes the characters), hears the ring tone of Doofenshmirtz, typically with the words \"Doofenshmirtz Evil Incorporated\", and is almost always sung by a quartet.<ref name=\"jcc\" group=\"epnote\">{{cite episode|title=Attack of the 50 Foot Sister|series=[[Phineas and Ferb]]| season= 2|episode= 51|credits=Writer: Jon Colton Barry, Piero Piluso; Director: [[Zac Moncrief]]|network=[[Disney XD]]}}</ref> Habitually, Doofenshmirtz's daily encounters with Perry follow a chain of events that routinely begins with a [[back-story]] told by Doofenshmirtz<ref name=\"Meap\" group=\"epnote\">{{cite episode|title=The Chronicles of Meap|series=Phineas and Ferb|number=59|season=2|network=Disney XD}}</ref><ref name=\"Plane\" group=\"epnote\">{{cite episode|title=De Plane! De Plane!|season=2|series=Phineas and Ferb|network=Disney XD}}</ref> and ends with Doofenshmirtz yelling his [[catch phrase]], \"Curse you, Perry the Platypus!\" Conveniently, he installs [[self-destruct]] buttons on everything he owns, which is usually how Perry destroys his creations. The residents of the town of Danville often mistake Doofenshmirtz for a pharmacist because he is always wearing a white lab coat. This theme was featured in a two-part 2014 Halloween episode entitled \"Night of the Living Pharmacists\".\n\n==Role in ''Milo Murphy's Law''==\n\nDoof makes a [[cameo appearance]] in the ending cliffhanger of the season finale of ''[[Milo Murphy's Law]]'', and tries to become a good guy throughout the [[Milo Murphy's Law#Season 2 (2019)|second season]].\n\n== Creation and design ==\n[[File:Dan Povenmire Comic-Con 2009.jpg|thumb|245px|Doofenshmirtz is voiced by ''Phineas and Ferb'' co-creator [[Dan Povenmire]].<ref name=\"podcast\"/>]]\nWhen [[Jeff \"Swampy\" Marsh]] and [[Dan Povenmire]] worked on the [[Nickelodeon (TV channel)|Nickelodeon]] animated series ''[[Rocko's Modern Life]],'' they always included a song/musical number and an action/chase scene. They wanted to incorporate this trait in \"Phineas and Ferb\",<ref name=\"AM2\">{{cite web|url= http://mag.awn.com/index.php?ltype=pageone&category2=&article_no=3534&page=2|title= From Swampy & Dan Emerges Phineas and Ferb\", Page 2.|author= Strike, Joe.|work= Animation World Magazine|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090821165941/http://mag.awn.com/index.php?ltype=pageone&category2=&article_no=3534&page=2|archivedate= 2009-08-21}}</ref> and used a platypus secret agent,<ref name=\"tampa\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tampabay.com/features/parenting/article993119.ece|title=Quick wit, funny characters drive ''Phineas and Ferb''|author=Robinson, Sherry|date=2009-04-18|accessdate=2009-08-16|work=[[St. Petersburg Times]]|location=[[St. Petersburg, Florida]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110607055650/http://www.tampabay.com/features/parenting/article993119.ece|archive-date=2011-06-07|url-status=dead}}</ref> due to its interesting appearance <ref name=\"QA\">{{cite news|url= http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/news/e3i0bc78baf8235f8b4159fd786ff9f8736|title= Q&A: Dan Povenmire|author= Bond, Paul.|date= 7 June 2009|work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> and role as a continuous nemesis that viewers could become familiar with.<ref>{{cite video|url=http://www.audiohollywood.net/Audio/phineas_ferb.mp3|title=\"Phineas and Ferb\" creators Dan Povenmire and Swampy Marsh|publisher=Audioholywood.net|medium=Audio interview|accessdate=2009-08-01|date=2009-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120301105638/http://www.audiohollywood.net/Audio/phineas_ferb.mp3|archive-date=2012-03-01|url-status=dead}}</ref> \"Dr. Meddleshmirtz,\" which later changed to Doofenshmirtz,<ref name=\"OPD\">{{cite video|title=Original Pitch featurette for Volume I|medium=DVD|people=Povenmire, Dan|publisher=[[Disney DVD]]}}</ref> was created in the same vein.\n\nEvery main character of the series was designed using the geometric shapes of  [[Tex Avery]]'s ''[[Looney Tunes]]'' graphic style in mind - Doofenshmirtz appears to be an [[oval]].<ref name=\"AM2\"/> The simplicity of the drawings were intended to allow child viewers to copy them easily. Each one was designed to be recognizable from a distance or, as Povenmire notes as a reference to [[Matt Groening]] and ''[[The Simpsons]],'' by [[silhouette]].<ref name=\"411 news\">{{cite web|url=http://www.resource411.com/411Update/Issue/Articles/Story.cfm?StoryID=1020 |title=Phineas and Ferb: Music, Mischief, And The Endless Summer Vacation |work=411 News |author=Galas, Marjorie |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090607043445/http://www.resource411.com/411Update/Issue/Articles/Story.cfm?StoryID=1020 |archivedate=2009-06-07 }}</ref>\n\n===Voice===\nCo-creator and executive producer Dan Povenmire voices Doofenshmirtz. He describes the voice he uses as \"Eastern European\" and is one he used at the age of fifteen while having pillow fights with his five-year-old sister. To this day, his sister recognizes the voice and asks him to do it frequently. During recording sessions, Povenmire is easily able to ad-lib and [[improvise]]; the writers can change his lines without throwing him off.<ref name=\"podcast\"/> Povenmire sometimes even adds his own lines or alters his enunciation{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}, and is usually asked to perform the voice in interviews.<ref name=\"podcast\"/>\n\n==Reception==\nDespite a negative review of the ''Phineas and Ferb'' series on ''Toon Zone'', Maxie Zeus notes that Povenmire's performance as Doofenshmirtz is a strong point of the series. Zeus states that \"Dan Povenmire voices him with such energy, and with such perfect timing, that you'll laugh out loud even at the stuff that isn't even ''supposed'' to be funny.\" Zeus also says that the Doofenshmirtz subplot would have made a \"fine bit of sketch writing\" if trimmed down.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.toonzone.net/articles/21300/phineas-and-ferb-spawn-of-frankenstein|title=\"Phineas and Ferb\": Spawn of Frankenstein|work=Toon Zone|last=Zeus|first=Maxie|date=February 1, 2008|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090822024814/http://news.toonzone.net/articles/21300/phineas-and-ferb-spawn-of-frankenstein|archivedate=August 22, 2009}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, Josh Jackson, editor-in-chief for ''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste Magazine]],'' wrote in a blog that ''Phineas and Ferb'' was \"the best kids show on TV\" and gave Doofenshmirtz a large amount of praise. Jackson calls his inventions \"awesomely designated devices of pure evil\" and his complex relationship with his nemesis Perry the Platypus as \"pitch-perfect.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pastemagazine.com/blogs/lists/2009/03/7-reasons-why-phineas-and-ferb-is-the-best-kids-sh.html|title=Five Reasons Why ''Phineas and Ferb'' is the Best Kids Show on TV|work=Paste Magazine|last=Jackson | first = John  |date=March 31, 2009}}</ref>\n\n==''Doof's Daily Dirt'' webseries ==\nIn January 2013, Doofenshmirtz \"launched [his] own YouTube channel and weekly videocast\" titled ''Doof's Daily Dirt''.{{efn|In one of the ''Doof's Daily Dirt'' videocasts, Doofenshmirtz admits that he chose Daily because of the title's [[alliteration]].}}  He comments on various [[Internet meme]]s and pop culture trends, usually long after the subject is no longer of interest or relevance. Subjects have included [[Facebook]], [[Internet slang|Internet Acronyms]], [[Lolcatz]], Bacon-infused products, [[Psy]]'s \"[[Gangnam Style]]\", [[One Direction]], [[Carly Rae Jepsen]]'s \"[[Call Me Maybe]]\", [[Here Comes Honey Boo Boo|Honey Boo-Boo]], the [[Keeping Up with the Kardashians|Kardashians]] and the [[Mayan apocalypse]]. He also started a Twitter account where he posts frequently.<ref name=\"wired\">{{cite web\n| url = https://www.wired.com/geekdad/2013/01/doofenshmirtz-daily-dirt/\n| title = Exclusive: Phineas and Ferb\u2018s Dr. Doofenshmirtz Launches Web Series, Twitter Account\n| last = Blum | first = Matt\n| work = Geekdad - Wired.com\n| date = January 4, 2013\n}}</ref> The webisode series had an original run of 13 episodes.<ref>{{cite web\n| url = http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/01/04/phineas-ferb-character-dr-doofenshmirtz-makes-his-social-media-debut-with-new-twitter-account-and-web-series/163984/\n| title = 'Phineas & Ferb' Character Dr. Doofenshmirtz Makes His Social Media Debut With New Twitter Account and Web Series\n| work = TV By the Numbers\n| last = Bibel | first = Sara\n| date = January 4, 2013\n}}</ref> He appeared in the season finale for the reality TV series ''[[Shark Tank]]'' to pitch his latest invention.<ref>{{cite web\n| url = http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2013/04/22/phineas-and-ferbs-nefarious-dr-doofenshmirtz-pitches-shark-tank-to-get-a-deal-for-his-latest-evil-inator-invention-820111/20130422disney01/\n| title = April 22, 2013\n| work = The Futon Critic\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2013/tv/news/phineas-and-ferb-villain-takes-pitch-to-shark-tank-in-disney-channel-abc-crossover-1200482912/|title=\u2018Phineas and Ferb\u2019 Villain Takes Pitch to \u2018Shark Tank\u2019 in Disney Channel-ABC Crossover|first=Marc |last=Graser|date=May 17, 2013|work=Variety|accessdate=9 July 2015}}</ref> The web series was renewed for a second season, but ultimately was ended after the cancellation of Phineas and Ferb.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2013/07/12/phineas-and-ferbs-breakout-internet-star-dr-doofenshmirtz-is-back-online-with-26-new-webisodes-for-summer-107515/20130712disney02/|title=Breaking News - \"Phineas and Ferb's\" Breakout Internet Star Dr. Doofenshmirtz Is Back Online with 26 New Webisodes for Summer|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|author=|date=|accessdate=9 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n'''Episode references'''\n{{reflist|group=\"epnote\"|40em}}\n\n'''Other sources'''\n{{Reflist|40em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{YouTube|u=doofdaily|Doof's Daily Dirt}}\n\n{{Phineas and Ferb}}\n{{Works by Dan Povenmire and Jeff \"Swampy\" Marsh}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Doofenshmirtz, Dr. Heinz}}\n[[Category:Phineas and Ferb characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional mad scientists]]\n[[Category:Fictional hunchbacks]]\n[[Category:Fictional inventors]]\n[[Category:Television characters introduced in 2007]]\n[[Category:Fictional American people of German descent]]\n[[Category:Animated human characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional immigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Male characters in animation]]\n[[Category:Milo Murphy's Law]]\n\n[[he:\u05d3\"\u05e8 \u05d4\u05d9\u05d9\u05e0\u05e5 \u05d3\u05d5\u05e4\u05e0\u05e9\u05de\u05d9\u05e8\u05e5]]\n", "name_user": "Layne.jpg", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dr._Heinz_Doofenshmirtz"}
